1
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:36,911
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:38,871 --> 00:00:39,956
Dad?

3
00:00:40,039 --> 00:00:41,123
Hi, Ui-yeong.

4
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:50,591
Alright.

5
00:00:55,721 --> 00:00:57,557
It's been a minute.

6
00:01:11,904 --> 00:01:13,030
Ui-yeong.

7
00:01:14,907 --> 00:01:16,033
Tae-seop.

8
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:18,703
Oh, you're here!

9
00:01:19,662 --> 00:01:21,539
- Come in.
- Yes, sir.

10
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:28,254
- Hello.
- Hello.

11
00:01:31,257 --> 00:01:32,258
Hey...

12
00:01:33,050 --> 00:01:35,386
What brings you here?
You didn't even call.

13
00:01:35,469 --> 00:01:39,849
Oh, I came to Seoul
for my friend's son's wedding.

14
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:46,188
I haven't been home in so long,
but it still feels like home.

15
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:49,191
That's a nice garden you built here.

16
00:01:51,944 --> 00:01:53,988
We keep running into each other.

17
00:01:54,071 --> 00:01:57,366
It seems like you're meant to be around
for a long time.

18
00:01:59,535 --> 00:02:00,953
How do they know each other?

19
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:03,080
Oh, Mom, that was...

20
00:02:03,497 --> 00:02:05,750
We ran into Dad in Sokcho.

21
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:08,127
- Sokcho?
- Yeah, I was there for a workshop.

22
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:11,380
I was so relieved to see Ui-yeong
with Tae-seop

23
00:02:11,589 --> 00:02:13,174
because I was worried

24
00:02:13,257 --> 00:02:16,469
she couldn't open up to a man
after being raised just by her mom.

25
00:02:17,511 --> 00:02:19,972
Don't say that.
I don't have any issue with that.

26
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:23,142
All things, like money, come and go,
so they don't matter.

27
00:02:23,225 --> 00:02:25,770
Just be by her side through it all,
like you are now.

28
00:02:26,395 --> 00:02:30,399
And Ui-yeong, don't hold yourself back
from doing things for your mom's sake.

29
00:02:30,816 --> 00:02:33,569
Don't worry. She has me by her side.

30
00:02:34,528 --> 00:02:36,405
Who's by my side?

31
00:02:43,579 --> 00:02:44,664
I know...

32
00:02:46,165 --> 00:02:49,001
I treated the two of you so poorly
back in the day.

33
00:02:49,877 --> 00:02:51,253
That's why I'm saying this.

34
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:55,549
I want to dedicate the rest of my life
to my family now.

35
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:58,177
I want to be by your side
at Ui-yeong's wedding.

36
00:02:58,469 --> 00:02:59,929
We have a lot of time left.

37
00:03:01,138 --> 00:03:02,473
Sometimes

38
00:03:04,892 --> 00:03:07,186
you just can't make up
for what you've done.

39
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:09,647
Whether I have a lot of time left or not

40
00:03:09,730 --> 00:03:12,191
I don't want to spend
a single second with you.

41
00:03:13,401 --> 00:03:14,402
Just go.

42
00:03:15,903 --> 00:03:18,989
Mom, Tae-seop is listening, too.

43
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:21,575
That's why he's acting like this.
How can I let it slide?

44
00:03:23,202 --> 00:03:24,995
It'll be good for him to know this sooner.

45
00:03:25,329 --> 00:03:28,833
This man and I have ended things
as husband and wife years ago.

46
00:03:28,916 --> 00:03:31,293
And I have no interest
in acting like a happy family.

47
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:34,171
- Mom!
- Get out!

48
00:03:35,381 --> 00:03:37,133
- My gosh.
- I'll leave if you don't.

49
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:39,135
Fine, I'll go.

50
00:03:40,052 --> 00:03:42,763
You really haven't changed a bit.

51
00:03:54,108 --> 00:03:55,234
Hey...

52
00:03:55,901 --> 00:03:58,654
Tae-seop, see you another time.

53
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:00,531
Mom...

54
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:11,333
I'm so sorry, Tae-seop.

55
00:04:16,797 --> 00:04:18,340
I'll call you later.

56
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:20,259
Sorry.

57
00:04:30,186 --> 00:04:31,187
Mom!

58
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:33,564
Why would you act like that
with Tae-seop here?

59
00:04:34,106 --> 00:04:37,359
How can you possibly see him again
after kicking him out like that?

60
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:40,112
I don't have to see him, then.
What else was I supposed to do?

61
00:04:42,406 --> 00:04:43,866
Let's talk about this later.

62
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,327
You were fine when you were lashing out.

63
00:04:46,410 --> 00:04:48,496
Are you suddenly in pain
now that I want to talk?

64
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:50,372
No, it's not like that...

65
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:53,209
That wasn't just for you to meet Tae-seop.

66
00:04:53,292 --> 00:04:55,085
It was also for him to get to know you.

67
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:57,129
Aren't you ashamed of yourself?

68
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:01,383
I don't even know how to face him
after that embarrassment!

69
00:05:02,718 --> 00:05:05,513
Is it so important for you
to impress others?

70
00:05:05,596 --> 00:05:06,931
Yeah, it is.

71
00:05:07,264 --> 00:05:10,142
I know you don't care about that
since you only care about yourself

72
00:05:10,559 --> 00:05:12,228
but Tae-seop is important to me

73
00:05:12,311 --> 00:05:14,939
so I care
about what he thinks of my family.

74
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:19,401
Why don't you just get a divorce
if you can't even stand to be around him?

75
00:05:20,027 --> 00:05:23,030
Why are you two even still together?

76
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:24,240
What did you say?

77
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:28,244
Mom, can't you think about me, too?

78
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:31,914
Only your opinions are always right,
and only your feelings matter to you.

79
00:05:32,289 --> 00:05:34,250
Catering to your every whim is

80
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:36,377
confusing and unbearable to me

81
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:40,130
sometimes, too.

82
00:05:41,006 --> 00:05:42,258
You can leave, too, then.

83
00:05:44,051 --> 00:05:45,719
- What?
- I live here

84
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:48,264
because I want to be at peace

85
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:50,182
so if you can't stand it, just leave.

86
00:05:54,186 --> 00:05:56,981
Fine, I'll leave.

87
00:06:27,344 --> 00:06:30,890
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 11

88
00:06:39,481 --> 00:06:41,191
SONG TAE-SEOP

89
00:06:44,945 --> 00:06:46,071
Hey, Tae-seop.

90
00:06:46,155 --> 00:06:48,699
Are you out right now?

91
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,079
Yeah.

92
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:55,998
Send me your location. I'll be right over.

93
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:05,090
Here, have some water.

94
00:07:06,634 --> 00:07:07,718
Thanks.

95
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:22,733
You must've been so startled today.

96
00:07:24,151 --> 00:07:27,029
No, I'm sure you're more startled
than I am.

97
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:32,868
My mom...

98
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:38,415
becomes extra sensitive
when it comes to anything about my dad.

99
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:42,711
He's basically Lord Voldemort
in the household.

100
00:07:45,923 --> 00:07:49,051
Why did Dad have to show up
out of the blue like that?

101
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:57,142
They really went too far today.

102
00:07:59,019 --> 00:08:00,771
Especially with you around.

103
00:08:04,149 --> 00:08:05,651
I'm really fine.

104
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:08,487
Today was just not meant to be.

105
00:08:11,448 --> 00:08:13,283
Let's stop thinking about it
and go to bed.

106
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:53,323
Dear Ms. Park, the florist said

107
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:55,826
that these flowers are a symbol
of nobility and respect.

108
00:08:56,326 --> 00:09:00,122
I promise to be my best self to Ui-yeong,
whom you've raised with love.

109
00:09:00,330 --> 00:09:01,623
I hope you'll approve of me.

110
00:09:48,504 --> 00:09:49,588
Hey, Tae-seop.

111
00:09:50,631 --> 00:09:52,925
Did you get some sleep?
You seemed bothered all night.

112
00:09:53,008 --> 00:09:54,968
Were you out?

113
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:56,804
I didn't even hear you leave.

114
00:09:57,012 --> 00:10:00,099
Oh, I went out to see the exhibition hall.

115
00:10:00,265 --> 00:10:02,267
There's a lot to check,
as it's starting soon.

116
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:04,603
Oh, the one where you're showcasing
your pieces?

117
00:10:04,686 --> 00:10:06,605
Yeah, you have to come, okay?

118
00:10:07,272 --> 00:10:08,482
Of course.

119
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:13,320
How's the chair designing going?
I can't wait to see it.

120
00:10:14,404 --> 00:10:16,865
You'll see it soon.
Come and check it out yourself.

121
00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:18,784
Okay.

122
00:10:19,368 --> 00:10:22,871
What's your plan today?
Are you returning home?

123
00:10:25,290 --> 00:10:26,291
No.

124
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:29,586
I'll stay at the hotel
for a few more days.

125
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:35,425
No need to do that.
Why don't you stay here for a while?

126
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:36,677
Here?

127
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,972
But I don't want to be a nuisance to you.

128
00:10:40,055 --> 00:10:41,765
I'll feel better that way.

129
00:10:47,896 --> 00:10:52,067
Okay, then.
I'll just stay for a few more days.

130
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:53,402
Okay.

131
00:10:53,610 --> 00:10:56,155
You must be hungry.
You haven't eaten since lunch yesterday.

132
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:58,240
Oh, have I not?

133
00:10:58,574 --> 00:10:59,950
I'm starving.

134
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:01,952
Let's share this.

135
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:05,122
Okay.

136
00:11:06,582 --> 00:11:07,666
Alright.

137
00:11:18,093 --> 00:11:20,304
I'll text you the password
for the door lock.

138
00:11:21,388 --> 00:11:23,515
- Okay.
- See you at home after work.

139
00:11:23,807 --> 00:11:25,267
- Drive safely.
- Okay.

140
00:11:26,059 --> 00:11:27,060
Bye!

141
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:30,063
Ui-yeong!

142
00:11:30,647 --> 00:11:31,648
Hello!

143
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:40,282
So, why is he driving you to work?

144
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:41,742
Oh, well...

145
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:55,088
It must've been so embarrassing for you.

146
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,299
What did Mr. Song say?

147
00:11:58,091 --> 00:11:59,968
He said it was fine.

148
00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:02,804
But I doubt my family left
a great impression on him.

149
00:12:05,599 --> 00:12:08,560
I had an argument with my mom
during the last Chuseok

150
00:12:08,644 --> 00:12:10,229
and only made up on the New Year's.

151
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:13,482
It took you months to make up?

152
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:16,526
Yeah, it happens
when you don't live together.

153
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:19,905
But it didn't bother me at all.
I'm used to it.

154
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:24,910
I know I argue with my mom a lot

155
00:12:24,993 --> 00:12:28,455
but it was never this bad,
so I don't know what to do.

156
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:32,042
I left in such a rush
that my socks don't even match.

157
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:33,877
Or my bras and undies.

158
00:12:35,003 --> 00:12:38,674
- You must've been too distracted.
- Yeah.

159
00:12:38,757 --> 00:12:42,177
I'm so glad Mr. Song offered
to let you stay at his place.

160
00:12:42,844 --> 00:12:44,888
Yeah, I'm really thankful for that.

161
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:46,723
It must be annoying for him

162
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:48,934
to live with someone
after being alone for so long.

163
00:12:49,559 --> 00:12:51,937
Check the depth of the platform
from a top view

164
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:53,855
and check the bridge length from the side.

165
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:55,649
Okay, noted.

166
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:57,776
Side...

167
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:00,237
Confusing, right?

168
00:13:00,821 --> 00:13:04,574
When we enter our sketch into the program,
it does the 3D modeling...

169
00:13:08,453 --> 00:13:09,663
Just use this, Sae-byeok.

170
00:13:11,206 --> 00:13:12,833
We'll have a big dinner after this.

171
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,710
- Please help me.
- Okay.

172
00:13:16,503 --> 00:13:18,547
Jin-su, let's start by cutting the pieces.

173
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:20,966
- Sae-byeok, please be our assistant.
- Okay.

174
00:13:21,091 --> 00:13:22,259
- Let's start.
- Okay.

175
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:33,854
See the numbers?
Line number one up with this.

176
00:13:34,062 --> 00:13:35,605
- And go that way.
- I see.

177
00:13:35,689 --> 00:13:37,357
Is this number two?

178
00:13:37,441 --> 00:13:39,901
Yeah, I've marked it,
so you can work with that, too.

179
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:42,446
- Check the ones in the back as well.
- The back.

180
00:13:42,529 --> 00:13:44,740
- Trace all of these.
- Okay.

181
00:14:04,593 --> 00:14:06,845
- Okay, okay.
- Let me take that.

182
00:14:06,928 --> 00:14:08,263
Should we call it a day?

183
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:12,559
You're having dinner with us, right?
There's a good diner down the street.

184
00:14:12,642 --> 00:14:14,978
I have plans. You two can go.

185
00:14:15,062 --> 00:14:16,063
Good work.

186
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:17,522
- You too.
- Thank you.

187
00:15:05,362 --> 00:15:09,741
SEPTEMBER 15, SUNDAY

188
00:15:27,759 --> 00:15:29,052
You came home early.

189
00:15:29,636 --> 00:15:31,638
I thought you'd come even later.

190
00:15:32,472 --> 00:15:33,682
What's all that?

191
00:15:34,349 --> 00:15:37,727
Our dinner and other things.

192
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:43,233
Here.

193
00:15:44,776 --> 00:15:46,903
Are all of these for me?

194
00:15:47,195 --> 00:15:49,448
Yeah, I know you couldn't pack much.

195
00:15:54,077 --> 00:15:55,245
You even got hair ties!

196
00:15:56,788 --> 00:15:57,998
I figured you'd need some.

197
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:01,376
Thanks. This is so cute.

198
00:16:03,044 --> 00:16:05,839
Oh, can you come this way?

199
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,305
You can hang your clothes here.

200
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:15,223
Oh, I'm fine...

201
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:18,018
I've invited you to stay here
to feel more at home.

202
00:16:18,101 --> 00:16:19,686
I don't want you to feel otherwise.

203
00:16:22,314 --> 00:16:23,440
Thank you.

204
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:30,614
- I like my eggs sunny-side up.
- Okay.

205
00:16:33,742 --> 00:16:34,910
- It's hot.
- Okay.

206
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:37,787
Hot!

207
00:16:47,672 --> 00:16:48,798
It smells so good.

208
00:16:51,092 --> 00:16:52,177
That looks amazing.

209
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:59,059
By the way

210
00:16:59,809 --> 00:17:03,897
how do you always know and prepare
exactly what I need?

211
00:17:05,941 --> 00:17:08,109
Because I'm always watching you.

212
00:17:10,737 --> 00:17:11,738
I see.

213
00:17:14,115 --> 00:17:17,536
Should we go for a walk after dinner?
Or watch a movie?

214
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:20,288
Everything sounds good.

215
00:17:24,584 --> 00:17:27,754
I'm always thinking
about what my client needs

216
00:17:27,921 --> 00:17:31,883
but I get to do what I want
in this exhibition, which is a challenge.

217
00:17:32,092 --> 00:17:34,928
Should we go to Pyeongchang
to see the leaves soon?

218
00:17:35,011 --> 00:17:36,680
- Pyeongchang? What about Dad?
- Yeah.

219
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:39,933
Why would he go?
It'll be more fun without him.

220
00:17:40,016 --> 00:17:41,643
Tell him to get some meat.

221
00:17:41,726 --> 00:17:43,562
I don't know. I feel...

222
00:17:45,772 --> 00:17:47,274
Should we get some ice cream?

223
00:17:48,066 --> 00:17:49,067
Sounds good.

224
00:18:02,831 --> 00:18:04,291
MOTHER

225
00:18:06,501 --> 00:18:08,169
You can pick up. I'll be quiet.

226
00:18:08,712 --> 00:18:09,796
Okay.

227
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:12,382
Hi, Mom.

228
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:14,342
Hey, Tae-seop, are you heading to work?

229
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:15,760
Yeah, I'm driving.

230
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:18,346
Let me make it quick, then.

231
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:21,641
It's our wedding anniversary this week.
You're coming, right?

232
00:18:21,725 --> 00:18:22,809
Oh...

233
00:18:24,185 --> 00:18:25,895
Yeah, what are you doing this year?

234
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:29,357
No idea. We spent too long thinking

235
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,318
about how to make it special.

236
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:34,779
It'll feel like a celebration,
as long as there's a cake and candles.

237
00:18:35,238 --> 00:18:37,949
Okay, I'll join you. Do you need anything?

238
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:39,826
No need to give us money or presents.

239
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,953
Just come and take some photos for us.

240
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:44,080
Your dad always zooms in too close
on my face

241
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:46,541
whenever I ask him to take photos for me

242
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:50,837
so I can't even tell
I'm traveling or at a party in them.

243
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,339
Okay, see you soon.

244
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:54,174
- Okay, see you.
- Bye.

245
00:18:59,012 --> 00:19:01,765
If they don't know what to do yet

246
00:19:02,015 --> 00:19:04,309
why don't you book a weekend
at the hotel for them?

247
00:19:04,392 --> 00:19:07,103
They can eat at the hotel restaurant
and stay overnight.

248
00:19:07,354 --> 00:19:09,856
That'd definitely be romantic.

249
00:19:10,815 --> 00:19:13,360
I can book a suite for them
using my employee discount.

250
00:19:15,445 --> 00:19:16,738
A hotel vacation?

251
00:19:17,572 --> 00:19:22,285
I just want to help you sometimes, too.

252
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:26,790
- Okay, let's do that, then.
- Okay.

253
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:32,837
Oh, has your mother called?

254
00:19:34,964 --> 00:19:36,007
Not at all.

255
00:19:37,175 --> 00:19:38,468
I knew it, though.

256
00:19:39,427 --> 00:19:41,471
I guess she's fine without me.

257
00:19:50,271 --> 00:19:51,898
- Hello.
- Hello.

258
00:19:51,981 --> 00:19:52,982
Hello.

259
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:57,862
- Hello.
- Hello.

260
00:19:57,946 --> 00:19:59,030
Hello, sir.

261
00:19:59,197 --> 00:20:00,865
There you are, Ji-su!

262
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:02,325
Yeah.

263
00:20:02,867 --> 00:20:04,828
- Did you eat?
- Yes, sir.

264
00:20:05,662 --> 00:20:06,955
Okay, go and get ready.

265
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,541
Oh, your mother's already here
and reading the script.

266
00:20:09,874 --> 00:20:12,460
- Sorry?
- She's making a special appearance.

267
00:20:13,169 --> 00:20:14,170
Did you not know?

268
00:20:24,931 --> 00:20:26,391
That's why I've made this choice.

269
00:20:26,808 --> 00:20:29,310
He needed to go to end this.

270
00:20:32,772 --> 00:20:33,857
What are you doing?

271
00:20:36,276 --> 00:20:38,945
My manager said
you were being treated poorly on set.

272
00:20:40,655 --> 00:20:42,824
- And whose fault is that?
- Exactly.

273
00:20:43,241 --> 00:20:45,535
I'm here
because I wasn't helping you enough.

274
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:47,954
I know you feel uneasy about me being here

275
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:50,248
but isn't it better
than ruining your career?

276
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:52,417
Jeong-a.

277
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,210
- Hey.
- Hello.

278
00:20:54,294 --> 00:20:55,295
Oh, there you are.

279
00:20:55,378 --> 00:20:58,381
It's a huge honor to work with you
on this project.

280
00:20:58,465 --> 00:21:00,133
- Thanks for the coffee.
- No worries.

281
00:21:00,216 --> 00:21:01,760
- Hello!
- Hi.

282
00:21:01,843 --> 00:21:05,805
I'm exhausted after a late-night shoot,
but seeing you gives me energy.

283
00:21:06,973 --> 00:21:08,600
- Please get changed and ready.
- Okay.

284
00:21:08,683 --> 00:21:09,809
- Let's go.
- Okay.

285
00:21:21,196 --> 00:21:24,699
One, two, three, cue!

286
00:21:24,908 --> 00:21:25,909
Ma'am!

287
00:21:26,534 --> 00:21:28,244
- Ma'am!
- Calm down!

288
00:21:28,369 --> 00:21:29,621
What happened?

289
00:21:29,704 --> 00:21:31,498
- Cut!
- Cut.

290
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:32,874
- Ji-su
- Yes.

291
00:21:32,957 --> 00:21:34,000
focus.

292
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:36,211
- From the top again.
- Yes, sir.

293
00:21:40,006 --> 00:21:44,260
One, two, three, cue!

294
00:21:45,845 --> 00:21:46,846
Ma'am!

295
00:21:47,931 --> 00:21:49,265
Just calm down!

296
00:21:49,390 --> 00:21:50,767
What happened?

297
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:52,519
- Cut!
- Cut.

298
00:21:57,690 --> 00:21:59,400
- Ji-su.
- Yes.

299
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:01,653
Are you nervous because your mom's here?

300
00:22:02,028 --> 00:22:05,532
This is a crucial moment
where we show your backstory.

301
00:22:05,740 --> 00:22:06,991
You have to nail it.

302
00:22:07,659 --> 00:22:09,160
Let's go from the top again.

303
00:22:10,161 --> 00:22:11,204
Yes, sir.

304
00:22:13,122 --> 00:22:14,249
Ji-su.

305
00:22:15,458 --> 00:22:17,752
Don't just pretend to look at me.
Actually look at me.

306
00:22:18,419 --> 00:22:21,673
So that we can exchange our emotions.
Okay?

307
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,721
I know you're going to try to protect
the kids.

308
00:22:31,432 --> 00:22:33,101
That's why I've made this choice.

309
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:37,230
He needed to go to end this.

310
00:22:39,274 --> 00:22:40,525
I'll help you.

311
00:22:40,608 --> 00:22:43,778
Our relationship ended ten years ago

312
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:45,947
when you left the orphanage.

313
00:22:46,614 --> 00:22:48,533
No need to feel like you owe me.

314
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:50,410
Make a fresh start

315
00:22:51,286 --> 00:22:52,537
and live your life.

316
00:22:53,246 --> 00:22:54,247
Ma'am!

317
00:22:54,455 --> 00:22:57,750
Sir, I can't testify
before this detective.

318
00:22:57,834 --> 00:22:59,586
- But wait!
- Let's get out.

319
00:23:00,253 --> 00:23:02,422
- Ma'am!
- Acting like this won't help.

320
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:04,299
- Ma'am!
- Let's get out.

321
00:23:04,382 --> 00:23:05,466
- Ma'am!
- Stop!

322
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:09,971
- Ma'am!
- Cut! Okay.

323
00:23:10,054 --> 00:23:11,222
Okay.

324
00:23:12,098 --> 00:23:14,183
I love this scene with the two of them.

325
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:15,685
It was really great.

326
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:18,396
Ji-su, you can be on standby now.

327
00:23:35,204 --> 00:23:38,499
Your acting's not too bad.

328
00:23:39,792 --> 00:23:42,045
You know being on standby is
a part of the job, right?

329
00:23:42,128 --> 00:23:46,591
I know it feels like a waste of time,
but there's so much to learn on the set.

330
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:51,054
You'll need an agency to support you
so you can focus on acting.

331
00:23:51,220 --> 00:23:53,556
Find one and give it your all.

332
00:24:05,902 --> 00:24:08,488
So, this is the cake
for the wedding anniversary?

333
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:13,034
Yeah, my boyfriend's mom requested it
to be a surprise.

334
00:24:14,077 --> 00:24:18,373
Don't people usually write
"Happy Anniversary" or "I love you"?

335
00:24:18,748 --> 00:24:21,626
I know.
But she chose this message herself.

336
00:24:22,669 --> 00:24:27,715
Isn't it so amazing
that they're still in love after decades?

337
00:24:28,341 --> 00:24:29,425
Yeah, it is.

338
00:24:30,301 --> 00:24:34,097
Maybe the message should've been in black
to make it more subtle.

339
00:24:35,306 --> 00:24:39,102
Do you remember
your parents' wedding anniversary?

340
00:24:39,310 --> 00:24:41,437
I can't remember the exact date.

341
00:24:41,771 --> 00:24:44,065
But it was peach season in the market.

342
00:24:45,066 --> 00:24:47,151
I guess you still celebrate it.

343
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:49,112
I didn't learn

344
00:24:49,195 --> 00:24:51,990
the idea of celebrating a marriage
while I was growing up.

345
00:24:52,073 --> 00:24:55,159
That's not a big deal.
Many families don't celebrate it.

346
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:56,494
Every culture's different.

347
00:24:56,577 --> 00:24:58,454
Oh, a cultural difference.

348
00:24:59,414 --> 00:25:01,624
Why don't you deliver the cake yourself?

349
00:25:01,708 --> 00:25:03,793
Your boyfriend's parents would love that.

350
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:07,630
Sure, I'll do that. Thank you.

351
00:25:09,966 --> 00:25:12,802
- Thank you, son.
- Thank you.

352
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:14,762
Enjoy.

353
00:25:15,054 --> 00:25:16,305
- This one's good.
- So good.

354
00:25:17,348 --> 00:25:18,683
Hello!

355
00:25:20,101 --> 00:25:21,144
Ta-da.

356
00:25:21,686 --> 00:25:23,646
Congratulations
on your wedding anniversary.

357
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:25,815
- Thank you.
- Thank you!

358
00:25:26,107 --> 00:25:27,483
You should join us for a bit.

359
00:25:27,567 --> 00:25:29,736
Yeah, come and have some cake with us.

360
00:25:29,819 --> 00:25:32,405
I've seen you around,
but we've never talked.

361
00:25:33,322 --> 00:25:36,743
I'll join you for a bit
since I'm still on duty.

362
00:25:42,331 --> 00:25:43,791
You can keep eating.

363
00:25:43,875 --> 00:25:45,168
Have some. It's amazing.

364
00:25:45,251 --> 00:25:47,003
- I'm glad.
- We love the food.

365
00:25:47,086 --> 00:25:48,671
One, two, three!

366
00:25:48,755 --> 00:25:49,797
UNTIL DEATH

367
00:25:51,340 --> 00:25:55,053
- Let's love each other until death.
- "Until death"!

368
00:25:55,136 --> 00:25:56,512
Until we're gone?

369
00:25:56,763 --> 00:26:00,892
Spending a weekend at the hotel is
such a treat. Thanks so much.

370
00:26:02,435 --> 00:26:04,187
Your parents are so lucky.

371
00:26:04,270 --> 00:26:06,564
Tae-seop's office is just noisy and dusty

372
00:26:06,647 --> 00:26:09,609
so we can't even visit him.

373
00:26:10,026 --> 00:26:13,279
My parents have never been here.

374
00:26:13,362 --> 00:26:14,405
- Really?
- Yeah.

375
00:26:14,489 --> 00:26:15,698
Why not?

376
00:26:15,782 --> 00:26:18,159
They'd be so happy to be invited.

377
00:26:18,701 --> 00:26:20,787
Do you want to take a photo together?

378
00:26:20,870 --> 00:26:22,789
Sure, take one for us.

379
00:26:22,872 --> 00:26:24,624
- Photos mean everything.
- Sounds good.

380
00:26:24,707 --> 00:26:26,250
One, two, three.

381
00:26:27,001 --> 00:26:29,087
One, two, three.

382
00:26:30,213 --> 00:26:31,214
All done.

383
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:33,925
- Join them. I'll take a family photo.
- What?

384
00:26:34,008 --> 00:26:36,219
- Yeah, come.
- Come here.

385
00:26:36,302 --> 00:26:37,553
One, two, three.

386
00:26:38,304 --> 00:26:39,430
And with the cake.

387
00:26:39,931 --> 00:26:42,225
Another one. One, two, three.

388
00:26:43,893 --> 00:26:45,061
They look great.

389
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:50,900
It'd be wonderful to take one
with all four of us.

390
00:26:50,983 --> 00:26:52,360
- I know.
- Gosh.

391
00:26:53,027 --> 00:26:54,487
Pass me your phone.

392
00:26:54,570 --> 00:26:56,823
I'll take one of you two.

393
00:26:56,906 --> 00:26:58,783
- Yeah, that sounds great.
- I'll take one.

394
00:26:58,866 --> 00:27:01,327
- Get closer!
- Yeah.

395
00:27:01,911 --> 00:27:03,746
- Beautiful.
- So handsome.

396
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:06,749
What a beautiful couple!

397
00:27:07,125 --> 00:27:08,209
Another one!

398
00:27:08,626 --> 00:27:09,836
Perfect.

399
00:27:10,002 --> 00:27:12,672
- That was perfect.
- Thank you.

400
00:27:13,548 --> 00:27:15,049
My gosh!

401
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:19,720
Nothing will beat this anniversary.
I'm so happy.

402
00:27:19,804 --> 00:27:22,223
You know, you say that every year.

403
00:27:22,306 --> 00:27:23,349
Do I?

404
00:27:24,892 --> 00:27:28,229
I mean it, though.

405
00:27:28,312 --> 00:27:30,690
The longer I live,
the more exciting life gets.

406
00:27:30,773 --> 00:27:32,692
I was so happy when it was us two

407
00:27:32,775 --> 00:27:35,027
even happier with Tae-seop

408
00:27:35,236 --> 00:27:37,947
and now that we have Ui-yeong too,
I feel like I have the world!

409
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:41,951
So, you two feel happy every day?

410
00:27:42,201 --> 00:27:43,870
Don't you ever fight?

411
00:27:43,953 --> 00:27:48,416
Oh, gosh, we fight all the time.

412
00:27:48,499 --> 00:27:50,751
No matter how close a couple seems

413
00:27:50,877 --> 00:27:54,297
- relationships can be like a maze.
- A maze?

414
00:27:54,380 --> 00:27:56,507
Yeah, it feels like

415
00:27:56,591 --> 00:27:57,758
- an empty void at times, too.
- Oh, an empty void.

416
00:27:59,051 --> 00:28:03,055
Trust me. I have many things
I can't tell Tae-seop.

417
00:28:03,139 --> 00:28:04,140
Whoa.

418
00:28:05,892 --> 00:28:09,937
But we're the perfect couple today.

419
00:28:10,021 --> 00:28:11,856
- I see.
- It's a happy day.

420
00:28:11,939 --> 00:28:14,442
- All thanks to you.
- It was nothing.

421
00:28:14,525 --> 00:28:16,777
- Thank you.
- Thanks so much.

422
00:28:17,612 --> 00:28:19,614
- I love you.
- Thank you, honey.

423
00:28:20,615 --> 00:28:23,117
I feel so happy!

424
00:28:26,287 --> 00:28:29,498
Tests for brain aneurysm are
so invasive and tough.

425
00:28:29,582 --> 00:28:31,417
Why did you come alone?

426
00:28:31,542 --> 00:28:33,961
I didn't think I needed to make
another person worried.

427
00:28:34,045 --> 00:28:35,463
I'll be fine.

428
00:28:35,755 --> 00:28:38,507
I understand
that you don't want to burden anyone

429
00:28:38,591 --> 00:28:41,093
but make sure to tell your loved ones
once you get tested.

430
00:28:41,510 --> 00:28:42,595
Okay.

431
00:28:42,678 --> 00:28:44,263
Tell me once the bag is done.

432
00:28:44,472 --> 00:28:45,514
Okay.

433
00:29:02,907 --> 00:29:04,533
Your parents

434
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:06,786
seemed happy today, right?

435
00:29:07,161 --> 00:29:08,162
Yeah.

436
00:29:08,996 --> 00:29:10,831
I didn't expect them to be so happy.

437
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:13,501
I guess I haven't been thoughtful enough
in the past.

438
00:29:14,126 --> 00:29:16,045
- Thank you.
- It was nothing.

439
00:29:19,257 --> 00:29:21,592
Is something bothering you?

440
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:22,927
Hmm?

441
00:29:23,552 --> 00:29:26,764
Oh, I just have a lot on my mind.

442
00:29:26,847 --> 00:29:28,307
About what?

443
00:29:30,685 --> 00:29:35,648
Are you okay with staying here like this?

444
00:29:38,150 --> 00:29:40,278
You must be going through a lot.

445
00:29:45,366 --> 00:29:48,369
I know you're waiting
for your mother to apologize

446
00:29:49,328 --> 00:29:53,749
but maybe your mother has
her side of the story, too.

447
00:29:54,041 --> 00:29:55,376
A story you don't know about.

448
00:29:57,586 --> 00:29:58,713
So

449
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:03,926
why don't you try
reaching out to her first?

450
00:30:08,931 --> 00:30:10,141
Just think about it.

451
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:13,561
I will.

452
00:30:35,207 --> 00:30:37,585
Are you sleepy?
Do you want the lights off?

453
00:30:41,797 --> 00:30:43,632
- Tae-seop.
- Yeah?

454
00:30:45,634 --> 00:30:47,511
I'll go home tomorrow.

455
00:30:49,180 --> 00:30:50,181
Hmm?

456
00:30:51,057 --> 00:30:54,852
As you said, it's not a good idea
to stay here for so long.

457
00:30:56,062 --> 00:30:58,147
I'll go home and talk to Mom.

458
00:31:00,441 --> 00:31:02,485
Good call.

459
00:31:03,402 --> 00:31:06,572
Should I drive you home after work?
You have a lot of stuff.

460
00:31:06,822 --> 00:31:09,450
No, you're busy with the exhibition.

461
00:31:09,533 --> 00:31:11,285
I can go by myself.

462
00:31:12,912 --> 00:31:17,416
Okay, I hope your talk with her goes well.

463
00:31:18,292 --> 00:31:19,293
Yeah.

464
00:32:43,919 --> 00:32:46,755
Why don't you just get a divorce
if you can't even stand him for a second?

465
00:32:46,839 --> 00:32:49,383
Why are you two even still together?

466
00:32:49,508 --> 00:32:50,676
You can leave, too, then.

467
00:32:50,759 --> 00:32:54,054
I live here because I want to be at peace

468
00:32:54,138 --> 00:32:56,056
so if you can't stand it, just leave.

469
00:32:57,308 --> 00:32:58,309
Fine

470
00:32:59,059 --> 00:33:00,144
I'll leave.

471
00:33:15,034 --> 00:33:17,578
It looks perfect.

472
00:33:17,661 --> 00:33:19,371
It looks prettier than in the blueprint.

473
00:33:23,709 --> 00:33:24,960
You're awfully quiet.

474
00:33:25,794 --> 00:33:27,171
Do you want to change something?

475
00:33:27,463 --> 00:33:28,797
No, it's not that.

476
00:33:31,008 --> 00:33:33,260
What would you want to do in this seat?

477
00:33:35,429 --> 00:33:38,265
Read a book and listen to music.

478
00:33:39,016 --> 00:33:40,768
It'll be great for some alone time.

479
00:33:40,851 --> 00:33:41,977
Right.

480
00:33:43,604 --> 00:33:45,981
What if I say I want to build another one?

481
00:33:47,191 --> 00:33:50,236
Oh? Didn't you say it was for lovers?

482
00:33:50,319 --> 00:33:52,029
- Yeah.
- So, you have two girlfriends?

483
00:33:52,196 --> 00:33:53,572
Of course not.

484
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:57,868
It's just that it seems lonely.

485
00:33:58,244 --> 00:33:59,787
It'd be nice to have another one.

486
00:34:00,871 --> 00:34:03,582
It shouldn't take as long
since we've already built one, right?

487
00:34:05,793 --> 00:34:07,962
If that's what you want

488
00:34:08,921 --> 00:34:10,881
- I'll get the wood.
- Okay.

489
00:34:57,595 --> 00:34:58,721
Hey, Tae-seop.

490
00:34:58,804 --> 00:35:01,724
Hey, Ui-yeong. I just got home from work.

491
00:35:01,890 --> 00:35:05,477
It feels so empty here without you.

492
00:35:06,186 --> 00:35:08,689
I guess I've already gotten
so used to having you around.

493
00:35:09,189 --> 00:35:10,232
Really?

494
00:35:10,316 --> 00:35:12,443
How did your talk with your mother go?

495
00:35:14,862 --> 00:35:17,573
I'll need to talk to her some more.

496
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:19,408
Glad it's going somewhere.

497
00:35:19,825 --> 00:35:22,369
- I'm sure it'll be sorted soon.
- Yeah.

498
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:23,996
Tae-seop

499
00:35:24,622 --> 00:35:26,874
I'm a bit tired today.

500
00:35:27,249 --> 00:35:28,876
I'm about to go to bed.

501
00:35:28,959 --> 00:35:30,461
Oh, really? Sorry.

502
00:35:30,669 --> 00:35:32,588
Go to bed. I'll call you tomorrow.

503
00:35:33,005 --> 00:35:34,006
Okay.

504
00:35:53,817 --> 00:35:56,654
Please take care of this by this week.

505
00:35:56,737 --> 00:35:57,780
Will do.

506
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:01,950
Yu-been! Don't carry everything at once.
You'll hurt yourself.

507
00:36:02,034 --> 00:36:03,077
Sorry.

508
00:36:03,160 --> 00:36:04,453
- Tae-seop.
- Yeah.

509
00:36:04,536 --> 00:36:06,622
We got the invitations from the gallery.

510
00:36:08,582 --> 00:36:11,460
You're going to the premiere
with Ui-yeong, right?

511
00:36:12,252 --> 00:36:13,253
As I should.

512
00:36:13,879 --> 00:36:17,091
I'll leave you two to it, then.

513
00:36:17,341 --> 00:36:20,052
I'll just go on a date with Sua, I guess.

514
00:36:27,351 --> 00:36:29,645
- Good work today.
- You too.

515
00:36:30,104 --> 00:36:31,730
- Jeong-a!
- Sir!

516
00:36:32,272 --> 00:36:33,607
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

517
00:36:33,691 --> 00:36:34,900
- I'll message you.
- Okay.

518
00:36:34,983 --> 00:36:35,984
- Bye.
- Bye.

519
00:36:42,783 --> 00:36:43,992
- Jeong-a!
- Hey.

520
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:48,038
Your husband's here.
He's been waiting for a while.

521
00:36:50,082 --> 00:36:51,291
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

522
00:36:57,881 --> 00:36:59,425
- Good work.
- Thanks.

523
00:37:10,060 --> 00:37:12,396
I didn't want to interrupt you at work

524
00:37:12,896 --> 00:37:16,150
but it was just too hard to reach you.

525
00:37:18,026 --> 00:37:19,069
Follow me.

526
00:37:49,933 --> 00:37:52,060
My lawyer must've told you everything
on my behalf.

527
00:37:52,144 --> 00:37:54,521
Aren't you the one
who refused to communicate?

528
00:38:06,283 --> 00:38:09,411
We have to look at each other's eyes
when we talk, no?

529
00:38:09,953 --> 00:38:10,954
Jeong-a

530
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:13,373
my feelings for you are real.

531
00:38:13,457 --> 00:38:16,251
What can I say to make you believe me?

532
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:20,255
You're the only woman in my life

533
00:38:21,632 --> 00:38:23,008
and think about our memories.

534
00:38:23,091 --> 00:38:26,762
All the trips we took, our conversations,
and our promises.

535
00:38:27,471 --> 00:38:30,098
They're all too real
to pretend they never happened.

536
00:38:30,182 --> 00:38:33,310
And they brought you so much joy.

537
00:38:33,769 --> 00:38:34,895
You were so happy.

538
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:41,360
But if that's not enough...

539
00:38:44,780 --> 00:38:47,199
I can also take something from you.

540
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:54,373
Once people hear
that we're getting divorced...

541
00:38:57,501 --> 00:38:59,002
you'll look like a laughingstock...

542
00:39:04,132 --> 00:39:05,551
to the public, no?

543
00:39:08,512 --> 00:39:10,222
Your tone is so gentle

544
00:39:11,056 --> 00:39:12,307
but not what you're saying.

545
00:39:12,641 --> 00:39:14,977
Sure, people will talk about me at first.

546
00:39:15,060 --> 00:39:17,813
But they'll soon realize
who was lying the whole time.

547
00:39:19,064 --> 00:39:21,525
Don't you think
I'd try to clarify things, too?

548
00:39:22,943 --> 00:39:25,362
Don't just assume I'll stay quiet
and let people talk.

549
00:39:26,864 --> 00:39:28,198
After all, it's not just me...

550
00:39:29,366 --> 00:39:30,701
who's at the peak of my career.

551
00:39:33,453 --> 00:39:35,622
Talk to my lawyer
if you want to talk, okay?

552
00:39:41,211 --> 00:39:42,379
What misunderstanding?

553
00:39:43,422 --> 00:39:45,048
So, what are you going to do?

554
00:39:45,465 --> 00:39:47,009
What do you want?

555
00:39:47,885 --> 00:39:49,386
Drag me down?

556
00:39:52,389 --> 00:39:53,390
Get out of my way.

557
00:39:55,309 --> 00:39:57,352
Don't you see me doing my best?

558
00:39:57,436 --> 00:39:58,729
How dare you?

559
00:39:58,812 --> 00:40:01,690
You think
a mediocre actress like you can hurt me?

560
00:40:03,442 --> 00:40:04,443
Let go!

561
00:40:04,526 --> 00:40:06,236
- Tell me!
- Let go!

562
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:09,781
Cut it out.

563
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:13,452
What the hell are you doing?

564
00:40:14,119 --> 00:40:15,245
Stopping you...

565
00:40:17,039 --> 00:40:18,540
from arguing with my stepmom.

566
00:40:20,042 --> 00:40:23,587
This is how your second marriage ends?
At last you're consistent, I guess.

567
00:40:27,716 --> 00:40:28,926
You...

568
00:41:25,107 --> 00:41:27,359
Ms. Son Jeong-a has checked in.

569
00:41:28,026 --> 00:41:30,070
Did she tell you beforehand?

570
00:41:30,487 --> 00:41:33,490
No, I'll check on her.
I'm at the hotel, anyway.

571
00:41:38,787 --> 00:41:41,164
Ms. Son, I heard you checked in
at the hotel.

572
00:41:41,248 --> 00:41:44,167
Let me know anytime if you need anything.

573
00:41:44,251 --> 00:41:47,629
MS. SON, I HEARD YOU CHECKED IN
AT THE HOTEL

574
00:41:53,427 --> 00:41:55,220
MS. SON JEONG-A

575
00:41:57,848 --> 00:41:58,974
Hello?

576
00:41:59,391 --> 00:42:02,686
I need someone to talk to.
Do you want to grab a drink with me?

577
00:42:11,069 --> 00:42:12,154
Hello.

578
00:42:12,279 --> 00:42:13,655
- Hey.
- Hi.

579
00:42:13,739 --> 00:42:15,032
- It's been a minute.
- Yeah.

580
00:42:15,240 --> 00:42:16,283
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

581
00:42:19,077 --> 00:42:20,245
What would you like?

582
00:42:22,330 --> 00:42:24,082
The same, please.

583
00:42:24,833 --> 00:42:25,917
She'll have the same one.

584
00:42:26,001 --> 00:42:28,128
Are you staying at the hotel
for a few days?

585
00:42:28,211 --> 00:42:29,254
No, just today.

586
00:42:29,921 --> 00:42:31,798
I felt too scared to be home alone.

587
00:42:32,841 --> 00:42:34,509
Are you still on duty?

588
00:42:34,801 --> 00:42:37,345
No, I just had a few things
to take care of.

589
00:42:37,429 --> 00:42:39,931
Sorry for being a nuisance
when you're still working.

590
00:42:40,015 --> 00:42:41,058
Not at all.

591
00:42:41,391 --> 00:42:42,934
Actually

592
00:42:43,185 --> 00:42:45,896
I've been staying at the hotel
for a few days.

593
00:42:51,568 --> 00:42:52,569
I'll leave this here.

594
00:42:53,195 --> 00:42:54,613
Oh? Ji-su.

595
00:42:59,826 --> 00:43:02,162
How do you two know each other?

596
00:43:03,413 --> 00:43:04,498
We're friends.

597
00:43:05,874 --> 00:43:07,334
Do you want to join for a drink?

598
00:43:08,168 --> 00:43:09,169
Have a seat.

599
00:43:11,046 --> 00:43:12,089
Sure.

600
00:43:28,355 --> 00:43:29,606
I think...

601
00:43:30,232 --> 00:43:32,818
I've experienced everything there is
in love now.

602
00:43:35,987 --> 00:43:38,824
Why did you argue with your mom?

603
00:43:38,907 --> 00:43:39,991
Oh...

604
00:43:42,911 --> 00:43:44,996
There was someone I wanted to impress

605
00:43:45,080 --> 00:43:49,084
and I didn't want to show him
how messy my family was

606
00:43:50,168 --> 00:43:52,712
but my mom just confessed everything.

607
00:43:55,966 --> 00:43:59,970
Life gets embarrassing at times.

608
00:44:00,053 --> 00:44:02,597
But we learn to forget
the embarrassment over time.

609
00:44:03,348 --> 00:44:07,060
I have a habit of only falling
for bad boys.

610
00:44:07,644 --> 00:44:08,687
It's embarrassing.

611
00:44:11,106 --> 00:44:14,317
So, does he not love you anymore?

612
00:44:15,152 --> 00:44:16,194
No.

613
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:20,699
I think I was more shocked than he was.

614
00:44:21,074 --> 00:44:22,993
I was just in denial.

615
00:44:23,493 --> 00:44:26,496
"They're not divorced,
just living separately."

616
00:44:26,913 --> 00:44:29,249
"I don't have many memories with him,
but I have a dad."

617
00:44:29,374 --> 00:44:32,043
"And as messy as it is, I have a family."

618
00:44:32,586 --> 00:44:34,546
I kept telling myself that to feel okay.

619
00:44:35,213 --> 00:44:38,175
You had to deal with this at some point.

620
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:41,136
It must've caught you off-guard

621
00:44:42,012 --> 00:44:43,680
but that won't change your life.

622
00:44:44,097 --> 00:44:47,809
In fact, you start thinking more
about what to do going forward

623
00:44:48,894 --> 00:44:50,562
once you face it.

624
00:44:54,983 --> 00:44:56,067
What about you?

625
00:44:56,401 --> 00:44:57,611
Do you have any secrets?

626
00:44:58,028 --> 00:44:59,362
Anything you're embarrassed of?

627
00:45:01,031 --> 00:45:02,157
No, I don't.

628
00:45:02,908 --> 00:45:05,118
Come on. You're so boring.

629
00:45:06,328 --> 00:45:08,455
Let's go now. You're drunk.

630
00:45:13,418 --> 00:45:16,922
You youngsters can go now.
The night is long.

631
00:45:17,964 --> 00:45:20,675
Have another drink. Goodnight.

632
00:45:20,759 --> 00:45:22,344
Okay, goodnight.

633
00:45:26,681 --> 00:45:27,807
Bye!

634
00:45:46,993 --> 00:45:48,578
You were really frustrated, huh?

635
00:45:51,081 --> 00:45:52,832
I just needed some fresh air.

636
00:45:54,668 --> 00:45:58,421
The window in my hotel suite is big
with a great view

637
00:45:58,713 --> 00:46:00,006
but it doesn't open.

638
00:46:01,132 --> 00:46:03,468
How's acting going for you?

639
00:46:04,844 --> 00:46:05,929
It's tough.

640
00:46:07,222 --> 00:46:09,266
But it's fun.

641
00:46:10,016 --> 00:46:12,936
I feel inspired to do better.

642
00:46:15,397 --> 00:46:16,564
I'm proud of you.

643
00:46:16,648 --> 00:46:17,816
Proud? You're funny.

644
00:46:18,441 --> 00:46:19,442
What am I? Your kid?

645
00:46:22,696 --> 00:46:25,949
Does Tae-seop know
you're with me right now?

646
00:46:27,534 --> 00:46:30,036
No, I couldn't tell him.

647
00:46:30,662 --> 00:46:31,913
Are you becoming like me now?

648
00:46:33,039 --> 00:46:35,292
Remember how you scolded me

649
00:46:35,375 --> 00:46:37,377
when I turned my phone off
and visited my mom?

650
00:46:39,879 --> 00:46:42,882
- You're right. I did that.
- Do you get it now?

651
00:46:44,426 --> 00:46:45,635
That's how humans are.

652
00:46:46,678 --> 00:46:50,724
We don't like being lonely,
but sometimes, we choose to be alone.

653
00:46:52,267 --> 00:46:53,601
Because that's the easiest way.

654
00:46:54,352 --> 00:46:56,354
Finding a good enough place to hide.

655
00:46:58,356 --> 00:47:01,943
But I felt happy and grateful
to have someone by my side.

656
00:47:04,988 --> 00:47:06,406
And I wanted to keep you.

657
00:47:10,952 --> 00:47:14,331
Weren't you hoping
Tae-seop would be like that for you?

658
00:47:15,373 --> 00:47:17,042
Yeah, I was.

659
00:47:23,006 --> 00:47:25,925
I'd better get going now.
I have a shoot tomorrow.

660
00:47:26,259 --> 00:47:27,886
Oh, yeah, you'd better go.

661
00:47:29,095 --> 00:47:30,138
Be happy.

662
00:47:31,181 --> 00:47:34,142
With whoever. In peace.

663
00:47:36,186 --> 00:47:37,187
You too.

664
00:47:38,521 --> 00:47:40,482
- Bye, then.
- Bye.

665
00:48:01,711 --> 00:48:02,754
I'd better go.

666
00:48:15,433 --> 00:48:17,519
Oh, hello, Ms. Park.

667
00:48:18,311 --> 00:48:19,938
- Hi, Tae-seop.
- Hi.

668
00:48:22,023 --> 00:48:25,110
- Let me help you.
- No, don't get your hands dirty.

669
00:48:25,193 --> 00:48:26,694
We can be done sooner if I help.

670
00:48:26,820 --> 00:48:28,446
- That way, right?
- Yeah.

671
00:48:39,791 --> 00:48:41,876
Your last visit must've been so jarring.

672
00:48:43,837 --> 00:48:46,464
Sorry for acting like that
after inviting you myself.

673
00:48:46,714 --> 00:48:47,966
It's fine.

674
00:48:48,049 --> 00:48:49,884
It's just between my husband and me

675
00:48:50,885 --> 00:48:53,638
so I hope you don't think badly
of Ui-yeong.

676
00:48:53,721 --> 00:48:55,640
I don't think badly of her at all.

677
00:48:57,684 --> 00:48:59,853
- How is she doing?
- Sorry?

678
00:49:02,397 --> 00:49:04,899
Oh, yeah, she's doing well. Don't worry.

679
00:49:05,233 --> 00:49:07,652
Thanks for being with her through this.

680
00:49:09,070 --> 00:49:13,116
It's getting late. You'd better head back.

681
00:49:13,575 --> 00:49:16,035
- Okay, I'll head back, then.
- Okay.

682
00:49:17,495 --> 00:49:18,538
Goodnight.

683
00:49:36,097 --> 00:49:38,641
FINDING DAILY HARMONY

684
00:49:44,689 --> 00:49:46,774
UI-YEONG

685
00:49:47,525 --> 00:49:48,610
Hey, Ui-yeong.

686
00:49:49,402 --> 00:49:53,865
I have something to tell you.
Can you come to where I am?

687
00:50:09,005 --> 00:50:11,382
I've been staying at the hotel
for the past few days.

688
00:50:12,383 --> 00:50:14,719
I haven't talked things out with my mom.

689
00:50:15,303 --> 00:50:17,639
Why didn't you just stay at mine
for a few more days?

690
00:50:18,890 --> 00:50:21,935
I've caused you enough worries.

691
00:50:22,352 --> 00:50:25,522
I would've really been a nuisance
if I stayed any longer.

692
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:29,609
Maybe I pushed you a bit too much.

693
00:50:29,692 --> 00:50:31,569
You just needed more time.

694
00:50:31,653 --> 00:50:33,696
It's fine.

695
00:50:35,031 --> 00:50:38,117
You have such a good heart.

696
00:50:38,910 --> 00:50:40,453
I felt

697
00:50:41,454 --> 00:50:43,331
like you wouldn't understand my feelings.

698
00:50:44,082 --> 00:50:46,376
And I was scared you'd think I was odd.

699
00:50:47,043 --> 00:50:51,339
You can patch things up with your mom
whenever you want, at your pace.

700
00:50:51,798 --> 00:50:52,799
But...

701
00:50:54,342 --> 00:50:55,927
just don't hide things from me.

702
00:50:57,178 --> 00:50:58,179
Okay.

703
00:51:00,390 --> 00:51:03,560
I'm really going to get in touch
with my mom tomorrow.

704
00:51:04,686 --> 00:51:07,897
I don't think
avoiding her like this is the answer.

705
00:51:09,857 --> 00:51:10,858
Okay.

706
00:51:11,859 --> 00:51:12,860
Oh.

707
00:51:15,822 --> 00:51:17,824
- Here.
- Oh, the exhibition!

708
00:51:18,491 --> 00:51:21,077
Right. It's premiering tomorrow, right?

709
00:51:21,327 --> 00:51:23,913
Yeah, but the exhibition is up
for a few days

710
00:51:24,706 --> 00:51:26,374
so let's go when you're free.

711
00:51:26,874 --> 00:51:27,875
Thank you.

712
00:51:29,168 --> 00:51:30,253
FINDING DAILY HARMONY

713
00:51:30,336 --> 00:51:31,337
I can't wait.

714
00:51:36,134 --> 00:51:37,427
They're this month's orders.

715
00:51:37,510 --> 00:51:39,137
- Sort them by this week.
- What?

716
00:51:57,739 --> 00:52:00,158
Mom, can we talk on the phone quickly?

717
00:52:20,845 --> 00:52:23,014
Hey, Ui-yeong.

718
00:52:23,723 --> 00:52:26,100
Are you okay to talk right now?

719
00:52:26,184 --> 00:52:28,269
Yeah, I'm fine.

720
00:52:28,353 --> 00:52:29,354
I see.

721
00:52:30,063 --> 00:52:34,734
Why don't we meet up and talk?

722
00:52:34,984 --> 00:52:36,736
Sure, sounds good.

723
00:52:37,236 --> 00:52:38,363
I also have...

724
00:52:39,197 --> 00:52:40,657
something to tell you.

725
00:52:41,741 --> 00:52:44,369
Do you want to come to the hotel
after work, then?

726
00:52:44,619 --> 00:52:47,121
I've never properly invited you here.

727
00:52:47,664 --> 00:52:50,124
Let's have a good dinner

728
00:52:50,917 --> 00:52:53,002
and have a long talk.

729
00:52:53,211 --> 00:52:54,629
- The hotel?
- Yeah.

730
00:52:55,088 --> 00:52:56,297
Okay, I'll be there.

731
00:52:57,215 --> 00:52:58,675
See you, then.

732
00:52:58,758 --> 00:53:00,677
- Okay, see you.
- Bye.

733
00:53:43,177 --> 00:53:45,179
Mom!

734
00:53:46,431 --> 00:53:47,515
Mom!

735
00:53:47,890 --> 00:53:50,435
What's going on? Open your eyes!

736
00:53:50,518 --> 00:53:52,937
Mom! Wake up!

737
00:53:53,396 --> 00:53:55,064
Can someone call the ambulance?

738
00:53:55,148 --> 00:53:57,442
Mom! Open your eyes!

739
00:53:57,692 --> 00:53:59,068
No, Mom!

740
00:53:59,152 --> 00:54:00,194
Mom!

741
00:54:16,502 --> 00:54:18,421
- Are you Ms. Park Jeong-im's guardian?
- Yes.

742
00:54:18,504 --> 00:54:21,048
We're doing an emergency CT scan.
Please wait.

743
00:54:44,197 --> 00:54:47,742
They painted this part darker...

744
00:54:47,825 --> 00:54:51,329
As you can see, this design is focused

745
00:54:51,412 --> 00:54:54,332
on achieving a natural texture.

746
00:54:54,707 --> 00:54:56,834
And the finishing is...

747
00:54:57,835 --> 00:54:59,378
There are so many impressive works.

748
00:54:59,545 --> 00:55:01,839
- I know.
- I'm getting nervous for you.

749
00:55:07,762 --> 00:55:09,096
Hey, Ui-yeong. Can you hear me?

750
00:55:09,263 --> 00:55:11,182
- I'm...
- Tae-seop.

751
00:55:13,851 --> 00:55:16,020
- What's wrong?
- It's my mom.

752
00:55:16,521 --> 00:55:18,439
I told her to come meet me at the hotel

753
00:55:18,689 --> 00:55:19,816
and she...

754
00:55:22,985 --> 00:55:24,362
fainted in the lobby.

755
00:55:25,321 --> 00:55:26,781
We're at the hospital right now.

756
00:55:26,864 --> 00:55:28,991
- Which hospital?
- Hankuk University Hospital.

757
00:55:29,075 --> 00:55:31,494
I'll come right over. Okay.

758
00:55:32,870 --> 00:55:34,580
But it's your turn to talk soon.

759
00:55:34,664 --> 00:55:36,290
I have to go. It's an emergency.

760
00:55:36,374 --> 00:55:38,334
Jin-su, please introduce the project
for me.

761
00:55:38,417 --> 00:55:39,502
- What?
- Sorry.

762
00:55:40,044 --> 00:55:41,087
Mr. Song!

763
00:55:42,296 --> 00:55:43,506
Mr. Song!

764
00:55:45,299 --> 00:55:46,425
You want to read it?

765
00:55:57,436 --> 00:55:58,521
Ui-yeong.

766
00:56:00,147 --> 00:56:01,399
Tae-seop...

767
00:56:08,114 --> 00:56:09,615
It's all my fault.

768
00:56:11,701 --> 00:56:16,038
This wouldn't have happened
if I just apologized to her.

769
00:56:17,164 --> 00:56:19,166
I made everything worse.

770
00:56:21,961 --> 00:56:23,296
It's not your fault.

771
00:56:24,797 --> 00:56:26,299
She'll be okay.

772
00:56:27,592 --> 00:56:28,843
Let's wait together.

773
00:56:36,767 --> 00:56:38,978
Cerebral aneurysm? My mom?

774
00:56:39,770 --> 00:56:42,565
I guess she didn't tell you.

775
00:56:42,648 --> 00:56:45,109
Is that what caused her to faint today?

776
00:56:45,192 --> 00:56:49,530
No, there was no ruptured aneurysm
or cerebral hemorrhage detected today.

777
00:56:49,614 --> 00:56:51,782
- I see.
- The sudden fainting

778
00:56:51,866 --> 00:56:54,827
could've been caused by stress
or other emotional factors

779
00:56:54,952 --> 00:56:56,662
so let her rest today

780
00:56:56,746 --> 00:56:59,373
and have her recover
at the hospital for a few days.

781
00:56:59,457 --> 00:57:01,083
- Okay, thank you.
- Sure.

782
00:57:01,167 --> 00:57:02,627
- Thank you.
- Let's go.

783
00:57:05,755 --> 00:57:08,090
How could you not tell me about this?

784
00:57:08,215 --> 00:57:09,300
My gosh.

785
00:57:10,009 --> 00:57:11,052
Are you okay?

786
00:57:11,135 --> 00:57:14,764
I just got dizzy out of nowhere
because I hadn't slept in a few days.

787
00:57:14,847 --> 00:57:16,015
I'm fine.

788
00:57:16,182 --> 00:57:17,850
Seriously.

789
00:57:20,853 --> 00:57:22,021
I'm really fine.

790
00:57:23,105 --> 00:57:25,733
Mr. Song, I introduced your project

791
00:57:25,816 --> 00:57:27,652
but don't assume that I did well.

792
00:57:27,777 --> 00:57:28,778
Thanks.

793
00:57:29,904 --> 00:57:31,364
Tae-seop!

794
00:57:32,114 --> 00:57:33,741
Today's the premiere, right?

795
00:57:33,824 --> 00:57:35,576
Oh, no. I'm so sorry.

796
00:57:35,660 --> 00:57:36,827
It's fine. Don't feel bad.

797
00:57:36,911 --> 00:57:39,914
You should go. Don't let me hold you back.

798
00:57:39,997 --> 00:57:41,749
Yeah, you can go now.

799
00:57:41,832 --> 00:57:43,376
We're fine now.

800
00:57:44,710 --> 00:57:47,838
- Okay, let me know if something happens.
- Okay.

801
00:57:48,130 --> 00:57:49,882
I'll get going, then.

802
00:57:49,966 --> 00:57:51,676
- Okay, thank you.
- Rest well.

803
00:57:51,759 --> 00:57:52,760
Thanks.

804
00:57:57,264 --> 00:57:58,599
Why are you smiling?

805
00:57:59,850 --> 00:58:01,143
You're ridiculous.

806
00:58:10,528 --> 00:58:13,489
I thought we'd be in bed together
at the hotel by now.

807
00:58:14,448 --> 00:58:15,825
But no, we're in hospital beds.

808
00:58:16,117 --> 00:58:17,368
This is good enough.

809
00:58:18,119 --> 00:58:20,871
It's a vacation at the hospital
instead of the hotel, right?

810
00:58:22,498 --> 00:58:23,833
That's not funny, okay?

811
00:58:24,291 --> 00:58:25,710
You know how scared I was?

812
00:58:25,793 --> 00:58:27,670
My heart is still pounding!

813
00:58:29,088 --> 00:58:31,298
I know we fought, but still.

814
00:58:31,632 --> 00:58:33,467
How could you keep this from me?

815
00:58:34,010 --> 00:58:35,886
I was going to tell you today.

816
00:58:35,970 --> 00:58:37,847
Sorry for the scary surprise.

817
00:58:39,265 --> 00:58:42,476
My timing's always terrible.

818
00:58:50,818 --> 00:58:51,986
Ui-yeong

819
00:58:53,654 --> 00:58:55,948
I can't tell you everything.

820
00:58:56,991 --> 00:59:01,579
But I spent too many days being lonely
by your dad's side.

821
00:59:03,205 --> 00:59:06,083
I tried arguing with him
and reprimanding him

822
00:59:07,585 --> 00:59:09,462
but learning to live with my loneliness

823
00:59:10,004 --> 00:59:14,383
was faster than changing his heart.

824
00:59:14,925 --> 00:59:16,343
Learning not to expect anything

825
00:59:17,386 --> 00:59:18,929
and not to rely on anyone again.

826
00:59:26,312 --> 00:59:28,898
But you still seemed like you needed a dad

827
00:59:29,690 --> 00:59:32,026
so I just ignored my own pain
and lived on.

828
00:59:33,486 --> 00:59:35,196
Seeing you grow up and thrive was

829
00:59:35,780 --> 00:59:37,531
good enough a motivation to live on.

830
00:59:42,828 --> 00:59:44,038
I finally felt...

831
00:59:44,705 --> 00:59:47,374
like life was getting comfortable

832
00:59:48,292 --> 00:59:50,211
but your dad showed up

833
00:59:50,294 --> 00:59:52,755
acting like nothing happened
and like a dad.

834
00:59:53,881 --> 00:59:57,468
That triggered
all my pent-up anger to burst.

835
00:59:59,011 --> 01:00:02,890
I'm sorry for putting you
in a difficult spot and for hurting you.

836
01:00:04,767 --> 01:00:05,893
Don't be.

837
01:00:07,603 --> 01:00:10,189
I was just mad that day.

838
01:00:11,649 --> 01:00:14,110
I didn't mean what I said.

839
01:00:15,111 --> 01:00:16,112
You know it, right?

840
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:19,406
You're all I have.

841
01:00:21,242 --> 01:00:22,701
And you're all I have.

842
01:00:28,749 --> 01:00:30,167
Be healthy.

843
01:00:30,751 --> 01:00:32,586
Gosh, fine.

844
01:00:34,713 --> 01:00:37,466
- When did my tiny girl grow up?
- My gosh.

845
01:00:43,430 --> 01:00:45,683
HANKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

846
01:00:46,225 --> 01:00:47,643
- You're leaving today.
- Yeah.

847
01:00:47,726 --> 01:00:50,187
You got lucky.

848
01:00:50,271 --> 01:00:52,481
It was a small cerebral aneurysm of 1.5mm

849
01:00:52,565 --> 01:00:55,151
and it's not in a spot
at a high risk of rupturing.

850
01:00:55,442 --> 01:00:59,029
Just come in to track it once a year
to keep it under control.

851
01:00:59,613 --> 01:01:00,698
Thank you.

852
01:01:01,407 --> 01:01:03,576
Is there anything we should be careful of?

853
01:01:03,659 --> 01:01:06,745
Don't overwork yourself
and get plenty of sleep at night.

854
01:01:07,121 --> 01:01:08,289
No drinking, either.

855
01:01:08,372 --> 01:01:11,709
Most importantly, do not get stressed.

856
01:01:11,792 --> 01:01:13,752
Don't get too anxious
about your conditions.

857
01:01:14,211 --> 01:01:15,212
Thank you.

858
01:01:15,296 --> 01:01:17,173
- Stress...
- Yes.

859
01:01:17,673 --> 01:01:18,674
Alright.

860
01:01:19,216 --> 01:01:21,635
- Mom, get some rest first.
- Okay.

861
01:01:23,345 --> 01:01:25,389
My gosh.

862
01:01:26,056 --> 01:01:27,474
We're home!

863
01:01:27,933 --> 01:01:29,143
It's so nice to be back.

864
01:01:29,351 --> 01:01:31,687
Gosh, that's nice.

865
01:01:31,770 --> 01:01:32,813
So nice.

866
01:01:33,772 --> 01:01:36,108
Did Tae-seop get home okay that night?

867
01:01:36,192 --> 01:01:38,068
Yeah, he did.

868
01:01:38,903 --> 01:01:41,197
When's the exhibition until?

869
01:01:41,280 --> 01:01:43,032
That? Until today.

870
01:01:43,574 --> 01:01:45,367
What? Are you sure you don't need to go?

871
01:01:45,451 --> 01:01:47,244
You're unwell. How can I leave you?

872
01:01:47,328 --> 01:01:51,707
The doctor doesn't even need to see me
for a year. Don't use me as an excuse.

873
01:01:51,790 --> 01:01:52,875
But still.

874
01:01:54,585 --> 01:01:57,796
Tae-seop seems like a good guy.

875
01:01:58,464 --> 01:02:01,717
- Why?
- I ran into him just outside.

876
01:02:03,385 --> 01:02:06,096
He came to tell me you were doing fine
so that I wouldn't worry.

877
01:02:06,180 --> 01:02:08,265
And he helped me with recycling.

878
01:02:09,016 --> 01:02:12,937
He's so good at removing the labels
before recycling plastic bottles!

879
01:02:13,520 --> 01:02:14,521
Really?

880
01:02:15,397 --> 01:02:16,607
Go.

881
01:02:16,857 --> 01:02:20,653
Whether it's the first or the last day,
I'm sure he wants you there.

882
01:02:21,779 --> 01:02:22,821
You think so?

883
01:02:24,281 --> 01:02:26,325
- You sure you'll be fine alone?
- Of course.

884
01:02:26,408 --> 01:02:27,910
Why are you being so clingy?

885
01:02:28,744 --> 01:02:29,745
Go.

886
01:02:44,802 --> 01:02:48,347
Mr. Song, would you like your furniture
delivered to the studio?

887
01:02:48,764 --> 01:02:51,684
No, I'll drive it myself
after we close today.

888
01:02:51,892 --> 01:02:52,893
Okay.

889
01:02:53,978 --> 01:02:57,064
I don't think anyone's coming.
Should we close early?

890
01:03:00,067 --> 01:03:01,068
Sure.

891
01:03:02,486 --> 01:03:03,529
Wait!

892
01:03:13,205 --> 01:03:14,248
I'm here.

893
01:03:25,301 --> 01:03:28,512
SEATS FOR LOVERS

894
01:03:28,595 --> 01:03:29,596
I see.

895
01:03:30,681 --> 01:03:32,725
This was why you needed...

896
01:03:33,767 --> 01:03:34,977
my height and all.

897
01:03:38,188 --> 01:03:40,482
I pay attention to a few details
when building chairs

898
01:03:41,150 --> 01:03:44,987
like its structural stability
and aesthetics.

899
01:03:46,030 --> 01:03:47,114
But this time

900
01:03:49,616 --> 01:03:51,660
- it was you.
- Hmm?

901
01:03:52,828 --> 01:03:54,455
I thought a lot about you.

902
01:03:55,789 --> 01:03:56,832
I see.

903
01:03:58,834 --> 01:04:02,588
I wanted these chairs to bring
a lot of conversation and understanding

904
01:04:02,671 --> 01:04:05,507
to you, me, and your loved ones.

905
01:04:07,176 --> 01:04:09,511
That was why I built two chairs as a pair.

906
01:04:10,971 --> 01:04:13,223
So, they're chairs of truth.

907
01:04:15,100 --> 01:04:17,519
I promise to tell you everything honestly

908
01:04:18,479 --> 01:04:22,232
when I sit in that chair from now on.

909
01:04:22,566 --> 01:04:23,567
Okay.

910
01:04:23,859 --> 01:04:25,569
But it's for you to handle what I say.

911
01:04:26,945 --> 01:04:27,946
Okay.

912
01:04:29,490 --> 01:04:30,783
With that said

913
01:04:31,575 --> 01:04:33,619
may I share what I think about the chairs?

914
01:04:33,994 --> 01:04:35,037
Huh?

915
01:04:35,704 --> 01:04:37,581
I'm getting nervous now.

916
01:04:43,337 --> 01:04:44,380
I love you.

917
01:04:46,340 --> 01:04:47,383
Sorry?

918
01:04:51,011 --> 01:04:54,223
I don't just like you.

919
01:04:55,432 --> 01:04:57,643
I love you deeply.

920
01:05:03,565 --> 01:05:06,360
The chairs showed me

921
01:05:08,320 --> 01:05:11,907
the way you look at me,
your worries about me

922
01:05:13,283 --> 01:05:16,161
and the love at the start of it all.

923
01:05:18,705 --> 01:05:21,875
So, I wanted to tell you.

924
01:05:24,461 --> 01:05:25,963
That's the best review...

925
01:05:27,589 --> 01:05:28,715
I've ever gotten.

926
01:05:51,613 --> 01:05:52,698
They look amazing.

927
01:06:19,057 --> 01:06:21,935
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

928
01:06:26,732 --> 01:06:29,943
I PROMISE TO BE MY BEST SELF TO UI-YEONG

929
01:06:34,198 --> 01:06:36,492
SO, WHY IS HE DRIVING YOU TO WORK?

930
01:06:36,700 --> 01:06:39,328
SEE YOU AT HOME AFTER WORK

931
01:06:40,537 --> 01:06:42,831
GIVE IT YOUR ALL

932
01:06:43,332 --> 01:06:46,001
UNTIL DEATH

933
01:06:54,468 --> 01:06:57,679
Was there a moment
when you realized you knew he was the one?

934
01:06:58,514 --> 01:07:01,767
Your friends also always talk
about getting married, right?

935
01:07:01,850 --> 01:07:05,562
Is your current boyfriend
not really husband material?

936
01:07:05,812 --> 01:07:07,439
You're definitely not car poor, then.

937
01:07:07,523 --> 01:07:08,690
- Mom!
- Hmm?

938
01:07:08,774 --> 01:07:11,151
So, you want to surprise her with a ring

939
01:07:11,443 --> 01:07:12,736
but don't know her size?

940
01:07:13,820 --> 01:07:15,322
My son...

941
01:07:15,405 --> 01:07:17,741
You wouldn't get married
if you could go back in time, right?

942
01:07:18,116 --> 01:07:20,702
So, I want to work
on a romance project next.

943
01:07:22,371 --> 01:07:24,540
Are you here for a blind date?

944
01:07:31,964 --> 01:07:33,966
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
